antihistamines me and my bf are ttc i am due any day now but having had some minor symptoms then there is a chance i could be pregnant this morning i took an antihistamine without having a second thought if i am pregnant could this be harmful to baby thanks in advance due my period any day now are antihistamines safe to take during pregnancy according to maternal fetal toxicology by koren most of the antihistamine compounds available over the counter have not been implicated in fetal or pregnancy problems a large study of exposure in pregnancy showed that only with diphenhydramine benadryl was there a significant association with fetal defect this medication was thought to cause an increased incidence of cleft lip and palate but recent studies have not been able to prove this the use of antihistamines in the first trimester does not appear to increase the risk for major birth defects as always it is important to discuss the use of any medication over the counter or prescription with your care provider Pregnancy Cephalic disorder Miscarriage Abortion debate Folic acid Fetal alcohol spectrum disorder Breastfeeding Congenital disorder Abortion Antihistamine Psoriasis Spina bifida Herpes simplex virus Abortion in the United States Turner syndrome Androgen insensitivity syndrome Tobacco smoking Hay fever Schizophrenia Cancer Fetus Premature birth Prenatal diagnosis Roe v. Wade Prolactinoma Menstrual cycle Psychosis Cytomegalovirus Biology and sexual orientation Cerebral palsy Multiple sclerosis Intact dilation and extraction Cleft Tocopherol Emergency contraception Paroxetine Breech birth Anencephaly Hypospadias Vitamin C Aspartame Clinical depression Atrial septal defect Paracetamol In vitro fertilisation Fluoxetine Oral contraceptive Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Autism Ectopic pregnancy Health issues and the effects of cannabis Chlorpromazine Coeliac disease Birth control Stroke Hyperemesis gravidarum Sickle-cell disease 